<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,654,1113]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Within Europe, two distinct subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[634,751,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="statices">
<emphasis box="[634,651,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[667,751,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">statices</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known, 
<taxonomicName authority="statices" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" box="[894,1103,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="statices" subSpecies="statices">
<emphasis box="[894,1103,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A. statices statices</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[1302,1369,690,716]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Spain</collectingCountry>
, most of central and eastern Europe to Siberia, 
<collectingCountry box="[668,748,726,752]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Turkey</collectingCountry>
all to 
<collectingCountry box="[824,895,726,752]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">China</collectingCountry>
. The other subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Alberti" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[1161,1409,726,753]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="statices" subSpecies="drenowskii">
<emphasis box="[1161,1409,726,753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A. statices drenowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the Balkans and 
<collectingCountry box="[539,619,762,788]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[634,875,762,788]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[752,808,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[1047,1251,762,791]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis box="[1113,1169,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[198,280,798,824]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
belong to the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="statices" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" box="[570,777,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="statices" subSpecies="statices">
<emphasis box="[570,777,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A. statices statices</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is in accordance with the material examined within this study. Literature records of this species are rather common (
<bibRefCitation author="Kranjcev, R." box="[931,1103,834,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="200 - 226" refId="ref9746" refString="Kranjcev, R. (1985) Odnos faune makrolepidoptera prema prirodnim i antropogenim stanistima Podravine i podravskih pijesaka (I). Podravski zbornik, 11, 200 - 226." type="journal article" year="1985">Kranjčev 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mladinov, L." box="[1116,1292,834,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10000" refString="Mladinov, L. (1958) 1 Popis nocnih leptira (Noctua) Zagreba i okolice. Hrvatski narodni zooloski muzej, Zagreb, 61 pp." type="book" year="1958">Mladinov 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mladinov, L." box="[1305,1364,834,860]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="89 - 99" refId="ref10053" refString="Mladinov, L. (1976) Lepidoptera iz doline gornjeg toka rijeke Kupe II. Bombyces i Sphinges. Acta entomologica Jugoslavica, 12, 89 - 99." type="journal article" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis box="[198,254,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). With this survey additional records are given but in overall the distribution in the country is rather well known (
<figureCitation box="[342,409,906,932]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,187,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-28@10.[151,1436,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution of Adscita statices in Croatia based on newly collected data and historical records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4643395/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). As it is a rather common and widespread species, it is not connected to a specific habitat but rather inhabits different habitats including dry, sandy, calcareous habitats as well as wet meadows and marshes (
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[205,448,978,1004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[324,381,978,1004]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). Still, almost all records from 
<collectingCountry box="[801,883,978,1004]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
are connected to the montane habitats, while the species is usually missing from lowland areas. This may be a bias as most of the “good” lowland habitats disappeared from 
<collectingCountry box="[341,426,1050,1076]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, which has also been reported in the butterfly diversity of the country (
<bibRefCitation author="Koren, T. &amp; Laus, B. &amp; Sasic, M. &amp; Mihoci, I. &amp; Stih, A. &amp; Bralic, P. &amp; Gomboc, S." box="[1222,1425,1050,1076]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="167 - 196" refId="ref9620" refString="Koren, T., Laus, B., Sasic, M., Mihoci, I., Stih, A., Bralic, P. &amp; Gomboc, S. (2017) Contribution to the knowledge of the butterfly fauna (Lepidoptera: Papilionoidea) of Hrvatsko zagorje, Croatia. Natura Croatica, 26, 167 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2017.26.15" type="journal article" year="2017">
Koren 
<emphasis box="[1301,1357,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Still, 
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[258,373,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="statices">
<emphasis box="[258,373,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A. statices</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be regarded as one of the most common 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[880,1009,1086,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Procridinae">Procridinae</taxonomicName>
species in the country.
</paragraph>
